# {{APP_NAME}}

A minimal Node script that runs one-shot inference against a local cartridge
via [`machineai-activation`](https://www.npmjs.com/package/machineai-activation).

## Get started

```bash
{{PACKAGE_MANAGER}} install
{{PACKAGE_MANAGER}} run build
{{PACKAGE_MANAGER}} start
```

The first run will download the cartridge into a local cache (`.machine-cache/`)
if it isn't already present. Subsequent runs reuse the cached weights.

## What's in `src/index.ts`

- `createMachine({ runtimes, cartridgeResolver })` — constructs the Machine,
  wiring a runtime (yours) to a cartridge resolver that pulls from the catalog.
- `machine.model({ cartridge: 'dev.machine.gemma-3n-e4b-it' })` — declares
  which cartridge your code wants. The resolver materializes it on first use.
- `generateText({ model, prompt })` — one-shot completion. Drop-in API shape
  matches the Vercel AI SDK and OpenAI SDK.

## Next steps

